[Yet again, we must thank Ramon for his excellent annual report on the state of anthrax in Argentina. I know that they struggle hard to get the herd owners in the high-risk districts in Buenos Aires Province to vaccinate their stock, but the lazy ones ably demonstrate the persistence of this pathogen in the optimum black soil habitat of this province. These ongoing cases just recontaminate their soils and undo any natural spore die off that has occurred.

Maps of Argentina can be found at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_pol96.jpg and http://healthmap.org/r/1yJb. A map of Buenos Aires Province can be found at https://maps.google.com/maps?q=map+buenos+aires+province. - Mod.MHJ]
